1
00:00:01,710 --> 00:00:03,712
<i>Stimulants, narcotics, cannabis.</i>

2
00:00:04,963 --> 00:00:07,090
<i>People who have used these drugs</i>

3
00:00:07,173 --> 00:00:10,719
<i>are now estimated</i>
<i>to total two million in Japan.</i>

4
00:00:11,219 --> 00:00:14,305
<i>The number of people arrested</i>
<i>for drug-related offenses</i>

5
00:00:14,889 --> 00:00:17,100
<i>is as many as 14,000 yearly.</i>

6
00:00:18,143 --> 00:00:20,854
What the hell did you do?

7
00:00:20,937 --> 00:00:22,272
No, I didn't--

8
00:00:22,355 --> 00:00:24,649
Hey! Drop the cheap act!

9
00:00:26,568 --> 00:00:28,361
Whose orders are you two following?

10
00:00:28,445 --> 00:00:29,863
Spit it out already.

11
00:00:32,574 --> 00:00:34,492
Why are you pissing in my office?

12
00:00:34,576 --> 00:00:36,494
You're getting the floor all filthy!

13
00:00:38,163 --> 00:00:40,915
I'm telling you
not to stain the damn floor!

14
00:00:54,971 --> 00:00:56,264
Don't move!

15
00:00:57,015 --> 00:00:58,141
Or he dies.

16
00:01:01,311 --> 00:01:03,772
What do we do with him?

17
00:01:03,855 --> 00:01:05,273
Guess we have to kill him.

18
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:07,734
But killing a narcotics agent…

19
00:01:07,817 --> 00:01:09,444
What other choice is there?

20
00:01:09,527 --> 00:01:10,403
Okay, sir.

21
00:01:15,992 --> 00:01:19,079
Would you please let me be an S for you?

22
00:01:19,162 --> 00:01:20,872
If you're really with the NCD,

23
00:01:20,955 --> 00:01:23,708
you'll have mutual coworkers
with the other NCD guy.

24
00:01:24,459 --> 00:01:27,504
If their numbers
are in both of your phones,

25
00:01:27,587 --> 00:01:28,880
I'll trust you.

26
00:01:28,963 --> 00:01:32,258
However, if they aren't…

27
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:35,762
it's over for you.

28
00:01:45,271 --> 00:01:46,231
Okay.

29
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:48,608
Okay. Is that so?

30
00:01:48,691 --> 00:01:49,692
All right.

31
00:01:50,652 --> 00:01:53,279
Okay, got it.

32
00:01:56,116 --> 00:01:59,536
There were no overlaps
between the data in this guy's phone

33
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:01,913
and the other NCD agent's phone.

34
00:02:01,996 --> 00:02:05,542
So they didn't have any
shared phone numbers in them?

35
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:06,459
Yes.

36
00:02:07,127 --> 00:02:08,336
Hey!

37
00:02:08,419 --> 00:02:10,213
So you were lying after all!

38
00:02:10,755 --> 00:02:13,341
If you're not with the NCD,
who exactly are you?

39
00:02:13,424 --> 00:02:14,384
I told you I'm--

40
00:02:15,135 --> 00:02:16,469
I've had it!

41
00:02:16,553 --> 00:02:17,804
I'm tired of this.

42
00:02:18,513 --> 00:02:19,639
Let's just kill him.

43
00:02:19,722 --> 00:02:21,474
Please listen to me.

44
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,935
Anything can happen in the field.

45
00:02:24,018 --> 00:02:27,021
Why would I have the numbers
of other agents in my phone?

46
00:02:27,105 --> 00:02:28,940
You just don't give up, do you?

47
00:02:29,023 --> 00:02:31,025
Then why did the other guy's phone

48
00:02:31,109 --> 00:02:34,612
have the phone number
of the NCD headquarters in it, huh?

49
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:35,822
That's because…

50
00:02:37,031 --> 00:02:40,910
he's a regular agent,
while I'm an undercover agent.

51
00:02:41,452 --> 00:02:43,288
I knew my phone could be checked.

52
00:02:43,371 --> 00:02:44,664
Oh, shut up.

53
00:02:44,747 --> 00:02:49,002
Okay, for the sake of argument,
let's say you really were an NCD agent.

54
00:02:49,085 --> 00:02:51,713
Why the hell do I have
to let you leave alive?

55
00:02:51,796 --> 00:02:53,214
I already told you!

56
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:56,259
I'll leak information
to the Saeki Family if you do.

57
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:58,219
And I told you I can't trust that!

58
00:02:58,303 --> 00:03:01,472
How do I know you won't betray me
as soon as I let you leave?

59
00:03:01,556 --> 00:03:03,057
I won't! I promise!

60
00:03:03,141 --> 00:03:05,059
Like I would take your word for it!

61
00:03:05,143 --> 00:03:06,102
Trust me!

62
00:03:06,185 --> 00:03:08,354
-I'm telling you I can't!
-Please!

63
00:03:14,235 --> 00:03:15,320
Fine.

64
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:21,284
If you want me to trust you,
prove it to me through your actions.

65
00:03:23,328 --> 00:03:24,287
What?

66
00:04:27,308 --> 00:04:28,434
Is he dead?

67
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:30,186
He's dead.

68
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:32,480
Kurosaki…

69
00:04:41,739 --> 00:04:43,074
Matsubara?

70
00:04:43,157 --> 00:04:47,370
Being a dealer for him was part
of your undercover investigation?

71
00:04:49,831 --> 00:04:50,873
Yes.

72
00:04:53,334 --> 00:04:54,460
The NCD guy?

73
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:57,463
We were about to deal with him.

74
00:04:57,547 --> 00:04:58,923
Uncover him.

75
00:04:59,007 --> 00:05:00,091
Yes, sir.

76
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:20,445
You kill him.

77
00:05:21,446 --> 00:05:22,280
What?

78
00:05:22,363 --> 00:05:23,823
You want my trust?

79
00:05:23,906 --> 00:05:25,783
Kill him with your own hands.

80
00:05:25,867 --> 00:05:28,578
Then I'll know you won't betray me.

81
00:05:28,661 --> 00:05:32,081
Because you'll be a murderer yourself.

82
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:35,460
Although…

83
00:05:38,087 --> 00:05:40,757
Is he even still alive?

84
00:05:46,095 --> 00:05:49,057
Still kicking, huh?
Sure you're not a junkie zombie too?

85
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:52,602
Come on, kill him!

86
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:09,994
You think you can take me out?

87
00:06:10,078 --> 00:06:11,704
Just try it!

88
00:06:13,790 --> 00:06:15,458
That hurts.

89
00:06:18,127 --> 00:06:20,505
I'll kill you before you kill me.

90
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:23,216
Damn it.

91
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:26,511
You asked for it.

92
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:31,724
You're swinging too wide!

93
00:06:31,808 --> 00:06:34,018
Are you even trying to hit him?

94
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:36,687
I won't go down easy.

95
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:39,649
Shut up, you half-dead asshole!

96
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:46,072
Die!

97
00:06:46,155 --> 00:06:48,157
Let's go for Saeki when we can.

98
00:07:03,673 --> 00:07:06,092
I'll kill every one of you.

99
00:07:11,472 --> 00:07:13,141
What a tough bastard.

100
00:07:13,224 --> 00:07:14,308
Give it.

101
00:07:19,605 --> 00:07:20,940
Use it.

102
00:07:21,023 --> 00:07:22,066
What?

103
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:24,152
Hurry up.

104
00:07:28,239 --> 00:07:30,366
Do as he says. Pick it up.

105
00:07:45,882 --> 00:07:46,841
My left abdomen.

106
00:07:46,924 --> 00:07:48,301
Stab it.

107
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:50,928
What are you saying? If I do that--

108
00:07:51,012 --> 00:07:54,515
Just do it!
It's the only way you can live!

109
00:07:55,683 --> 00:07:56,642
Five.

110
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:58,144
Four.

111
00:07:58,686 --> 00:07:59,687
Three.

112
00:08:00,188 --> 00:08:00,980
Two.

113
00:08:01,063 --> 00:08:02,023
I can't.

114
00:08:02,648 --> 00:08:04,108
I can't do it.

115
00:08:06,569 --> 00:08:07,528
One.

116
00:08:13,075 --> 00:08:14,452
Well, shit.

117
00:08:14,535 --> 00:08:17,205
-Shinichi, Shinji. Kill him.
-Yes, sir.

118
00:08:23,586 --> 00:08:24,545
Huh?

119
00:08:26,589 --> 00:08:28,966
Yes, that's good.

120
00:08:29,717 --> 00:08:30,801
You're--

121
00:08:31,594 --> 00:08:35,431
With this, you'll earn their trust.

122
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:36,516
Why?

123
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:42,104
So you do have it in you.

124
00:08:43,272 --> 00:08:44,524
Why do that…

125
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:45,608
Shut up.

126
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:47,568
Don't say any more.

127
00:08:48,653 --> 00:08:50,238
What, he's still alive?

128
00:08:50,321 --> 00:08:51,989
-Hey.
-Yes, sir.

129
00:08:57,787 --> 00:08:58,788
Fucking bastard!

130
00:09:00,414 --> 00:09:01,290
I knew it!

131
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:03,751
Let's go!

132
00:09:09,715 --> 00:09:10,883
That asshole!

133
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:12,510
Don't let them escape! Jump!

134
00:09:12,593 --> 00:09:13,553
From here?

135
00:09:13,636 --> 00:09:15,054
Just jump!

136
00:09:15,137 --> 00:09:16,639
No way!

137
00:09:16,722 --> 00:09:18,849
Go that way then! Fucking useless wimps!

138
00:09:19,809 --> 00:09:21,102
You all right?

139
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:26,732
-I'm gonna fall!
-You go too!

140
00:09:26,816 --> 00:09:29,652
-Don't! Please!
-You jump too, come on!

141
00:09:39,078 --> 00:09:40,580
You shouldn't have done that.

142
00:09:40,663 --> 00:09:42,373
What else was I supposed to do?

143
00:09:42,456 --> 00:09:43,416
Leave me.

144
00:09:43,499 --> 00:09:44,458
What?

145
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:48,087
The bleeding looks bad,
but the left abdomen has no vital organs.

146
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:49,088
What?

147
00:09:49,171 --> 00:09:52,633
It was to make them trust you.
You're so damn useless.

148
00:09:52,717 --> 00:09:54,510
Then tell me that!

149
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:56,178
Stop!

150
00:09:58,598 --> 00:10:00,099
You go ahead.

151
00:10:00,182 --> 00:10:01,392
I can't leave you.

152
00:10:01,475 --> 00:10:03,603
Then they'll kill us both!

153
00:10:03,686 --> 00:10:06,063
Run away and call the NCD!

154
00:10:20,453 --> 00:10:21,579
Kurosaki.

155
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:34,717
Too bad for you.

156
00:10:36,344 --> 00:10:37,928
Get up.

157
00:10:42,558 --> 00:10:43,643
Hey.

158
00:10:46,354 --> 00:10:49,023
Take them back up,
and let's finally end all this.

159
00:10:49,106 --> 00:10:50,024
Yes, sir.

160
00:10:50,107 --> 00:10:51,275
Stand up, asshole.

161
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:01,619
You're such a useless S.

162
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:05,206
You forced me into being an S.

163
00:11:05,289 --> 00:11:07,792
This is all your fault.

164
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:08,959
Yes.

165
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:13,964
But I promise you,
I'll get you out of this alive.

166
00:11:14,048 --> 00:11:15,549
Don't give up.

167
00:11:16,425 --> 00:11:19,011
I don't know, I think this is it.

168
00:11:23,265 --> 00:11:24,475
What the…

169
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:35,277
Oh, man.

170
00:11:36,737 --> 00:11:40,282
Rough day for the NCD's Mad Dog, isn't it?

171
00:11:41,117 --> 00:11:42,785
Who the fuck are you?

172
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,371
Katsuragi.

173
00:11:47,915 --> 00:11:49,250
The police.

174
00:11:53,003 --> 00:11:54,672
-Arrest them all.
-Yes, sir.

175
00:12:06,851 --> 00:12:09,103
-What's your problem?
-Don't resist.

176
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:12,773
Damn punk.

177
00:12:14,191 --> 00:12:15,192
Start walking.

178
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:16,694
Get off me!

179
00:12:27,663 --> 00:12:28,581
Fucker!

180
00:12:39,216 --> 00:12:40,259
Hey.

181
00:12:42,303 --> 00:12:43,137
Start walking.

182
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:44,388
Hands off me.

183
00:12:45,764 --> 00:12:47,808
Too bad for you.

184
00:12:47,892 --> 00:12:50,019
This case belongs to the police.

185
00:12:52,146 --> 00:12:53,939
Police mutt.

186
00:13:00,154 --> 00:13:02,156
Ministry mutt.

187
00:13:04,658 --> 00:13:07,328
Hey, call an ambulance, quick.

188
00:13:07,411 --> 00:13:09,079
Keep it down.

189
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:11,373
He won't die even if you kill him.

190
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:13,167
-Hey.
-Yes, sir.

191
00:13:15,085 --> 00:13:16,295
Can you move?

192
00:13:28,599 --> 00:13:31,185
How long did you know
something was going on?

193
00:13:32,186 --> 00:13:35,314
Since you got kidnapped
from the bay parking lot.

194
00:13:35,814 --> 00:13:39,193
That suit has a wiretap
and a GPS tracker hidden in it.

195
00:13:41,904 --> 00:13:42,988
What are these?

196
00:13:43,072 --> 00:13:45,824
I want you to infiltrate the Saeki Family.

197
00:13:48,035 --> 00:13:50,037
So you knew everything.

198
00:13:51,121 --> 00:13:53,582
Then you knew what was happening inside.

199
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:55,459
Why didn't you come sooner?

200
00:13:56,919 --> 00:13:59,296
To fatten the pigs before the slaughter.

201
00:13:59,922 --> 00:14:01,006
What did you say?

202
00:14:01,882 --> 00:14:03,801
This was the real end goal.

203
00:14:03,884 --> 00:14:06,053
That's why I waited until the last moment.

204
00:14:06,136 --> 00:14:09,265
And guess what?
Now, I can even get them for murder.

205
00:14:09,848 --> 00:14:12,393
Under the Organized Crime Punishment Act,

206
00:14:12,476 --> 00:14:15,771
we can now go arrest
the entire organization.

207
00:14:17,231 --> 00:14:19,149
Fuck that!

208
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:21,485
What do you take people's lives for?

209
00:14:23,070 --> 00:14:28,534
While you were trying to rack up points,
we were about to get killed!

210
00:14:40,004 --> 00:14:41,463
Results mean everything.

211
00:14:42,131 --> 00:14:44,842
I don't care about the life
of a punk like you.

212
00:14:46,427 --> 00:14:47,595
But well,

213
00:14:47,678 --> 00:14:52,558
you did do a relatively
decent job as an S this time.

214
00:14:53,142 --> 00:14:56,270
Sure. How about I treat you
to some <i>okonomiyaki?</i>

215
00:15:03,777 --> 00:15:05,195
Damn you.

216
00:15:26,842 --> 00:15:28,135
Kurosaki!

217
00:15:31,221 --> 00:15:32,348
Where are we?

218
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:35,476
That's not what matters right now.

219
00:15:35,559 --> 00:15:39,063
If you got treated any later,
you could've died of blood loss!

220
00:15:39,146 --> 00:15:41,523
Why do you always act so selfishly--

221
00:15:41,607 --> 00:15:42,733
What?

222
00:15:42,816 --> 00:15:45,110
Were we able to arrest them?

223
00:15:48,656 --> 00:15:49,990
Well…

224
00:15:51,075 --> 00:15:52,576
the police took them all.

225
00:16:00,834 --> 00:16:02,169
Kurosaki.

226
00:16:03,295 --> 00:16:05,631
Have some faith in us too for once.

227
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:17,851
Their obsession with the junkies
made them blind to everything else.

228
00:16:19,311 --> 00:16:20,854
What incompetent fools.

229
00:16:22,481 --> 00:16:24,900
I'll let the higher-ups
know about this case.

230
00:16:26,068 --> 00:16:27,695
Thank you, sir.

231
00:16:27,778 --> 00:16:28,696
On that note,

232
00:16:29,238 --> 00:16:33,367
can we get the bigger smuggling ring
that the Saeki Family was working with?

233
00:16:35,369 --> 00:16:36,537
Well, about that…

234
00:16:38,372 --> 00:16:39,206
What is it?

235
00:16:40,749 --> 00:16:42,918
We searched the Saeki Family premises,

236
00:16:43,752 --> 00:16:47,297
but their computers had been wiped,
and we didn't find any USBs either.

237
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:50,884
How did that happen?

238
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:55,639
I believe they might have wiped it
as soon as the NCD got in there.

239
00:16:57,224 --> 00:16:58,058
No.

240
00:16:59,184 --> 00:17:01,520
They got into the office first,

241
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:05,482
so the NCD might have done it.

242
00:17:06,066 --> 00:17:07,401
But that's…

243
00:17:08,736 --> 00:17:10,946
The agent's name was Kurosaki, wasn't it?

244
00:17:12,072 --> 00:17:14,158
He's got a pretty keen nose.

245
00:17:14,742 --> 00:17:17,536
He's always wherever the drugs are.

246
00:17:18,328 --> 00:17:19,872
Keep track of him,

247
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:24,376
and beat the NCD to the punch
on every single case from now on.

248
00:17:24,877 --> 00:17:25,753
Yes, sir.

249
00:17:28,714 --> 00:17:30,049
Know this, Katsuragi.

250
00:17:31,175 --> 00:17:35,095
It's the police that protect
this country from threats,

251
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:37,347
not the NCD.

252
00:17:38,557 --> 00:17:39,933
Don't forget that.

253
00:17:41,268 --> 00:17:42,311
Yes, sir.

254
00:18:03,832 --> 00:18:05,667
You look terrible.

255
00:18:07,461 --> 00:18:09,671
Hey, you listening?

256
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:14,510
Get out, you useless S.

257
00:18:16,512 --> 00:18:18,472
Who's useless again?

258
00:18:24,019 --> 00:18:25,104
And that is?

259
00:18:27,815 --> 00:18:29,066
COPYING FOUR ITEMS

260
00:18:33,153 --> 00:18:34,154
Hello, sir!

261
00:18:34,655 --> 00:18:36,281
Where's Shinichi and Shinji?

262
00:18:41,328 --> 00:18:42,329
Here.

263
00:18:45,082 --> 00:18:48,293
It has info on not just
the underlying organization,

264
00:18:48,377 --> 00:18:51,296
but also the client list,
their smuggling routes,

265
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:53,590
and their past transactions too.

266
00:18:58,470 --> 00:18:59,429
You…

267
00:19:01,765 --> 00:19:04,268
I wouldn't say no to a compliment.

268
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:10,149
You did great.

269
00:19:12,484 --> 00:19:15,821
Wait, I didn't think
you would actually compliment me.

270
00:19:19,074 --> 00:19:20,367
You did great.

271
00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:27,207
Hey, knock it off.

272
00:19:39,136 --> 00:19:40,846
Man, it hurts.

273
00:19:44,892 --> 00:19:48,687
<i>Ryu Saeki, the leader of the Saeki Family,</i>

274
00:19:48,770 --> 00:19:52,065
<i>a drug smuggling organization</i>
<i>and organized crime group,</i>

275
00:19:52,149 --> 00:19:54,985
<i>was found dead in his jail cell.</i>

276
00:19:55,819 --> 00:19:59,198
<i>The police are investigating it</i>
<i>as a potential suicide.</i>

277
00:19:59,907 --> 00:20:05,120
<i>The Narcotics Control Department</i>
<i>is also investigating the case,</i>

278
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:08,749
<i>expecting a larger smuggling ring</i>
<i>to be behind the Saeki Family.</i>

279
00:20:09,249 --> 00:20:10,626
<i>The police also say</i>

280
00:20:10,709 --> 00:20:17,716
<i>that several persons of interest related</i>
<i>to this case have reportedly gone missing.</i>

281
00:20:17,799 --> 00:20:21,678
<i>There may be more to come</i>
<i>in regards to this drug smuggling case.</i>

282
00:20:22,471 --> 00:20:24,306
<i>On to our next news,</i>

283
00:20:25,349 --> 00:20:30,229
<i>there was a fire today in Kokuryocho,</i>
<i>Chofu City, at the Marsan Apartments.</i>

